  "conclusion": "After the rowchunk leading-GEMV fix, full-native/no-rowchunk behavior is unchanged in the important way: c4 with native context+native O output remains red on row3 ([137,137,137,118]), forced batch_gemv O output alone remains red on row0 ([82,137,137,137]), and per-row context-only replay with native O output remains the c4 full-native diagnostic that turns green ([137]*4). Combining context-only replay with batch_gemv O output is red ([137,104,137,137]), so the rowchunk O-projection repair is not a retained full-native fix and should not be applied to no-rowchunk c4. c8 likewise remains red with batch_gemv O output and with context-only+batch_gemv ([82,137,137,137,45,11,137,137] and [137,104,137,137,45,11,83,137]). The remaining retained blocker is native grouped full-attention context/pre-QKV/no-rowchunk behavior, not the rowchunk O path. No throughput claim is made.",
